Literature.Author: Zhang DL, Guan RZ, Huang WS, Xiong J..2013
Literature.Title: Recombinant expression, affinity purification and functional characterization of Scots pine defensin 1.

Sequence Information.Comments: Discovery: Derived from hemoglobin, a proteolysis product. Isolated from liver. APD analysis reveals the sequence is most similar (38.5%) tofish Oreoch-1.Activity: Active against E. tarda. At 83.72 uM, it killed S. aureus, M. lysodeikticus, E. tarda and V. harveyi (MBC 83.72 uM); at 41.86 uM, it killed A. caviae, A. hydrophila, 70% A. jandaei, A. veronil, V. alginolyticus, and V. parahaemolyticus (MBC 41.86 uM). Replaced 12/2017; updated 7/2021.
